{"asset_id": "asset_708b6078b844d64004d51221", "problem_id": "prob_19d16e9ace2cc7979576cf43", "asset_type": "text", "asset_role": "question_text_source", "source_uri": "source://seephys/train[300:600]/0/question", "storage_uri": "inline://prob_19d16e9ace2cc7979576cf43/question_source", "file_format": "txt", "file_size_bytes": 665, "width": null, "height": null, "sha256": "840d0f24185893e0cd40a0d62bfa05ee5dd326ba89b4e4eab0ff08440e932bad", "perceptual_hash": null, "source_text_snapshot": "A d.c. electromagnet is to be constructed by winding a coil of $N$ turns tightly on an iron yoke shaped like a doughnut with a small slab sliced out to form the gap as in Fig. 2.34. The radii for the doughnut are $a$ and $b$ and the width of the gap is $W$. The permeability $\\mu$ for the iron can be assumed constant and large. A wire of radius $r$ and resistivity $\\rho$ is to be used for the coil. The completed magnet will be operated by placing the coil across a d.c. power supply of voltage $V$. For simplicity, assume that $b/a \\gg 1$ and $a/r \\gg 1$. Derive expressions for the following quantities: The steady state value for the magnetic field in the gap.", "normalized_text_snapshot": null, "text_completeness_score": 0.8, "blur_score": null, "readability_score": null, "noise_score": null, "cropped_from_asset_id": null, "roi_bbox": null, "unit_normalization_map": [], "variable_aliases": [{"original": "A", "canonical": "A", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "d", "canonical": "d", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "c", "canonical": "c", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "is", "canonical": "is", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "to", "canonical": "to", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "be", "canonical": "be", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "by", "canonical": "by", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "a", "canonical": "a", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "coil", "canonical": "coil", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "of"